{
  "text": "The advantages of this parametrization are that it contains the maximum number of positive semi-definite bilinear combinations of the g \u03b3 \u01eb\u00b5 and that the Q \u01eb\u00b5 are directly interpretable as the total probabilities for \u00b5-handed muons to decay into \u01eb-handed electrons [4] . Furthermore, experimentally it is found that Q LL is close to unity. Thus, if Eq. (4) is used to eliminate Q LL , the 9 remaining variables are all close to zero. The bilinear combinations Q RR , Q LR , Q RL , B LR , B RL , I \u03b1 , I \u03b2 were adopted in the global analyses presented in [4, [CITATION_1] 11] .",
